Frequently asked questions
What is web hosting, and why do I need it?
Web hosting is a service that hosts websites for clients on their servers. Web hosts often provide different server types and software, such as a website builder or easy CMS integration, to create sites to get online. So choosing a web hosting provider that caters to your particular needs and tech skillset is important. For example, the tools you get with Spaceship Web Hosting solutions make it easy to go through the process of domain registration, get online, and build your online presence. Your online presence is essential for your brand, and everything you do on the Internet makes all the difference to how your brand is represented.
How do I choose the right web hosting plan for my website?
We provide various reliable web hosting solutions tailored to different needs, including three shared hosting plans — Essential, Pro, and Supreme — as well as Virtual Private Server (VPS) hosting — Starlight™ Virtual Machines. Select a plan based on your website’s specific requirements. Choosing a data center close to your target audience to optimize loading speeds can greatly enhance site performance. Our data centers for shared hosting are strategically located in the US, Asia, Europe, and the UK. For more control and flexibility, our VPS offers dedicated resources within a shared environment, delivering a balance of cost-effectiveness and high performance.
How does shared hosting work?
Considered the most affordable web hosting option, shared web hosting offers enough resources for any startup, local business, or personal website. Shared hosting is an entry-level type of web hosting where one physical server hosts multiple websites, and often hundreds of users. Since each user shares a section of an individual server to host their website files, keeping costs low is easy. Users share on-demand system resources and receive a percentage of databases, disk space, CPU, RAM, and FTP accounts. Other resources include the single MySQL server and LiteSpeed server.
How to manage shared hosting?
The Hosting Manager for your Spaceship account is where you can manage everything connected to your hosting subscription and launch your website in no time. You can also upgrade or downgrade your plan easily, check resources, and add domains, SSL certificates, and mailboxes to your hosting account, among other things. For advanced features and setup, you can use cPanel, which comes with our shared hosting plans. In cPanel, you'll be able to build your website, upload and manage files and databases, and install scripts.
Can I host multiple websites on a single hosting plan?
Yes. All our hosting plans support multiple websites. Here’s how it works:
  • Essential plan – Host up to 5 domains or subdomains.
  • Pro and Supreme plans – Host an unlimited number of domains and subdomains.

Regardless of your plan, you can create unlimited websites within your hosting subscription by uploading content to different folders in your account. Each folder functions as a separate website. If you start with the Essential plan, you can upgrade anytime to a higher plan in just a few clicks when you need more resources.

Is Spaceship shared hosting cloud-based?
Yes, we enjoy all the advantages of cloud-based shared hosting. These include increased performance, distributed storage, greater reliability, and cloud architecture based on NVMe SSD storage disks. Designed to handle a variety of hardware and software-stack failures, Cloud storage reinforces your data with an extra layer of protection by distributing it across various servers. Featuring zero downtime and the highest performance, it provides you with the utmost stability.
Can I use WordPress with Spaceship shared hosting?

Yes, with Spaceship Hosting Manager you can install WordPress in just a few clicks.

Note: WordPress AI Tools is designed to work only with new WordPress installations. If you already have an existing website built on WordPress, you won’t be able to use the AI Launch or Site Assistant features. However, you can still install the plugin to browse the Design Library and get layout inspiration and guidance.

Are WordPress AI Tools and Website Builder included for free, and how do they differ?

All shared hosting plans include Website Builder at no extra cost. Website Builder is a solution powered by SiteJet that combines a powerful low-code/no-code web builder with collaboration tools integrated into cPanel. It also features AI writing assistance, making it ideal for a seamless and efficient web-building experience without relying on WordPress.

On the other hand, WordPress AI Tools comes pre-installed with WordPress at no extra cost for Supreme and Pro plans during the Unbox™ process. This is a native site creation experience built entirely on core WordPress components, maintaining full compatibility with WP plugins, themes, and WooCommerce. The builder includes: AI Launch, AI Site Assistant, and Design Library. For more details, visit our guide.

Choose your preferred builder and start creating right away.

How many visitors can Web Hosting handle?
Each website is different and the amount of traffic they can handle will depend on the resources each visitor is using. A very efficiently coded website that uses a small amount of resources per visitor can allow a large number of visitors to visit the site at one time. But a poorly or inefficiently coded website may allow only a small number of visitors simultaneously. How many visitors your site can handle is largely determined by how your site is coded. Thanks to the cloud architecture our shared web hosting service is based on, the servers deliver high performance, high availability, and can sustain a large number of visitors.
Is shared hosting suitable for e-commerce?
Although there are some limitations, shared hosting for those starting an online store is an excellent choice. Large e-commerce businesses may find there are not enough applications available and access to server resources is limited. But for most businesses in e-commerce, shared hosting is more than enough to suit requirements.
How secure is my website with your hosting services?
Spaceship’s ​​secure web hosting is protected by a firewall and strong security features. Enjoy shared hosting with built-in security. All Shared Hosting plans come with Imunify360, a comprehensive shared hosting security suite that actively safeguards your website. It includes:
  • Free malware protection for websites, including real-time scanning and cleanup.
  • Advanced built-in website firewall protection.
  • Proactive defense against zero-day attacks.
  • Intrusion detection and prevention.
  • Reputation management to help keep your domain from blacklists.

Even so, we advise our customers to use secure usernames and passwords, regularly scan computers and websites, use a secured FTP connection, and keep website scripts, plugins, and themes versions up-to-date.

Additionally, Spaceship provides secure shared hosting that can help protect against DDoS attacks on the server level to help keep your service running. We use both application-layer and low-level network security to limit or block abusive connections. Features include:
  • Rate limiting.
  • Blackholing.
  • Intrusion detection and prevention system.
  • Web application firewall.
  • HTTP-sessions pattern analysis.

Note: These measures are used to help protect servers, and do not include individual website protection. If you are looking for individual DDoS protection for your website, please consider purchasing it from a trusted vendor.

What are the EU, UK, and Singapore hosting, and how much does such web hosting cost?
Choosing a hosting server location close to your audience—such as in the EU, UK, or Singapore—can significantly improve your website’s loading speed, user experience, search engine rankings, and SEO. With Spaceship’s shared hosting plans, you can select from data centers in these regions at no additional cost:
  • EU and UK Hosting: Ideal for serving audiences in Europe, the UK, and Africa. Hosting in these locations ensures faster website performance and localized data storage, making it a reliable and efficient solution.
  • Singapore web server hosting: Perfect for Asia-based audiences. Our Singapore data center offers low-latency for audiences in this region, reliable service powered by 100% renewable energy, and is certified to ISO 14001 and ISO 50001 standards, ensuring sustainability and exceptional website performance.
How do I transfer my existing website to your hosting platform?
Migrating your website to Spaceship is quick, easy, and free during the Unbox™ process — no technical skills required. Simply upload your cPanel backup file (tar.gz or zip, up to 20GB), let the system check its compatibility, and restore your data. You will need to manually connect your domains in Hosting Manager. Just ensure your backup includes all essential website data, files, and databases. Emails must be migrated separately after setting up accounts in Spacemail, and SSL keys need manual installation, though you get free SSLs with shared hosting. Only MySQL and MariaDB databases are supported for migration. A stable internet connection is recommended for a smooth process.
What kind of customer support can I expect?
We offer 24/7 support to assist you whenever you need help. Our dedicated support team can address inquiries within their scope of expertise and access. Additionally, our AI assistant, Alf, is also available and continuously improving to provide even better assistance over time.

Disclaimers

Our Supreme plan offers unmetered disk space, intended only for your website. This space must be used in accordance with our Acceptable Use Policy (AUP), and in particular the Disk Usage Provision paragraph.

Our CPU and RAM resource limits are for burst allowance, which helps your website cope with high traffic. This allowance is only for a limited time, as shown in our AUP.

Spacemail is provided free with Web Hosting for one year. It can be used with domains but not with subdomains.

Spaceship provides unlimited free SSL certificates for Pro and Supreme Web Hosting plans, and 5 SSL certificates for Essential Web Hosting plans. When hosting subscriptions are canceled, the free SSL certificates are automatically canceled.

The transfer of hosting accounts to Spaceship must be completed by the customer. Our support team can provide additional guidance if it’s needed.

Cloud storage architecture used on our shared servers should not be confused with cloud hosting.

Our advertised discount offer only applies to purchases of annual and biennial plans. This discount offer does not apply to renewals.
